# OpenClaw Future Config Patch
## Memory Embedding with Local gemma-300M
## Apply after updating to OpenClaw 2026.3.x+

{
  "memory": {
    "embedding": {
      "provider": "local",
      "model": "gemma-300m",
      "fallback": ["gemini", "openai"]
    },
    "indexConcurrency": 4,
    "deltaThreshold": {
      "bytes": 102400,
      "messages": 50
    }
  }
}

## Installation commands for future version:
# openclaw memory install-embedding --provider local --model gemma-300m
# openclaw memory status --deep

## Features this enables:
# - Local embeddings (zero API cost)
# - No OpenAI fallback unless local fails
# - Parallel batch operations (4 concurrent)
# - Auto re-index at 100KB or 50 messages
